-- Gordhan Says South Africa Doesn't See Need for Further Stimulus Measures
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2010-10-21T11:27:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/gordhan-says-south-africa-doesn-t-see-need-for-further-stimulus-measures.html
South African Finance Minister
Pravin Gordhan said the country’s government sees no need for
further stimulus measures and that interest rates at a record
low will help to support an economic recovery.  The government is not factoring in a “double-dip” global
recession, he said in a written reply to questions in
Parliament, e-mailed today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in Cape Town at 
